Section 1:
HB2247 FA2 WaldronJo-AQH(Untimely Filed)
3/12/2025 3:34:39 pm
FLOOR AMENDMENT
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
State of Oklahoma
SPEAKER:
CHAIR:
I move to amend HB2247
Page Section Lines
Of the Engrossed Bill
By deleting the language of Section 1 in its entirety and by inserting in
lieu thereof the following language:
"The State Department of Education shall make available written guidance
and procedures about the least restrictive environment requirements set
forth in the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA), the
federal regulations implementing the IDEA, and binding legal precedents
issued by the United States Supreme Court and the United States Court of
Appeals for the Tenth Circuit. The purpose of the guidance and procedures
shall be to aid Individualized Education Program (IEP) teams in making
least restrictive environment decisions for Oklahoma students with
disabilities in compliance with the law.”
AMEND TITLE TO CONFORM TO AMENDMENTS
Amendment submitted by: John Waldron
